Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.40,0:01:34.11,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,The forthcoming "Promised Day".
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.15,0:01:40.37,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,People are continuing to prepare for the day that will determine their fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.99,0:01:46.04,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Time passes by, and it is now spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.04,0:01:49.29,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,At last, the Promised Day is about to arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.13,0:01:59.72,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Some sort of festival?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.72,0:02:03.10,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,It's the Festival of the Sheep, a local specialty of Resembool that takes place every spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.93,0:02:07.85,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to ask something like this on an important day, but we'd like to replenish our water supplies.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.85,0:02:08.89,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Sure thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.89,0:02:10.27,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Have all the water you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.56,0:02:12.44,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Bring out the water tanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.32,0:02:17.11,Default,Sol2,0000,0000,0000,,One, two...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.86,0:02:18.82,Default,Sol2,0000,0000,0000,,There.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.13,0:02:38.80,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like there's no one home.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.93,0:02:41.14,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Here we are, miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.07,0:02:58.53,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Home sweet home.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.62,0:03:07.33,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, this place is full of automails.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.54,0:03:09.45,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't touch the ones that aren't finished yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.05,0:03:23.97,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,It's so dusty in here...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.69,0:03:40.28,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.99,0:03:43.57,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Edward Elric?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.20,0:03:46.24,Default,Gor,0000,0000,0000,,Intruders?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.12,0:03:48.29,Default,Gor,0000,0000,0000,,Oww!!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.04,0:03:51.79,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are you guys doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.04,0:03:52.96,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Lin?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.92,0:03:56.17,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,If I recall, you two are working for Kimblee!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.17,0:03:56.79,Default,Gor,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.96,0:04:00.67,Default,Gor,0000,0000,0000,,You guys are... from Briggs!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.34,0:04:03.13,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You chased us all the way down here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.47,0:04:05.93,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Wait! Wait! Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.93,0:04:06.68,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Put down your guns!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.68,0:04:10.18,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Hey Ed... just {\i1}what{\i0\fscx40} {\r} is going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.18,0:04:12.85,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Long story.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.85,0:04:15.44,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, what were you doing in my room?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.73,0:04:18.61,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I just wanted to eat while enjoying the outside view every once in a while!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.61,0:04:20.78,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I said, put down your gun!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.78,0:04:22.24,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,Quit yelling!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.90,0:04:24.61,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,This dog is so loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.11,0:04:28.66,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Get the hell out of my room!!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.84,0:04:42.30,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,You had me worried sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.88,0:04:44.01,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.01,0:04:46.13,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Glad to see you're safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.13,0:04:48.10,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,A-Al isn't with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.72,0:04:53.06,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Al's at the station!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.06,0:04:54.60,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,He's with Major Miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.31,0:04:56.77,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,But they're about to depart soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.77,0:04:58.61,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,If you hurry, you may be able to make it in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.90,0:05:05.95,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.57,0:05:07.66,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you going to go see him?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.49,0:05:12.95,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We're fugitives wanted by Central.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.20,0:05:16.25,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It would be bad if someone were to see us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.29,0:05:18.42,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.43,0:05:32.26,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,The Festival of the Sheep, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.85,0:05:34.31,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Sure brings back memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.69,0:05:38.10,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to be departing soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.65,0:05:39.44,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.03,0:05:47.95,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you will have found your body by the next time you return to this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.03,0:05:50.03,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.71,0:06:06.88,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,Winry?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.39,0:06:13.47,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.01,0:06:15.22,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.68,0:06:18.06,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for worrying you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.40,0:06:23.11,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like we have more of you dowdy people in here now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.11,0:06:25.53,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for causing such a ruckus earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.90,0:06:28.57,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,We're soldiers from Briggs.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.57,0:06:31.28,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,We were dispatched as Miss Winry's bodyguards.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.57,0:06:34.95,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,You're Lin... right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.95,0:06:35.99,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.99,0:06:37.95,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,You know this dude?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.58,0:06:41.92,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,The name's Greed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.92,0:06:42.96,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet ya.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.54,0:06:45.59,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.93,0:06:54.60,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,And so, these guys are currently working for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.60,0:06:56.35,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,What made you come here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.35,0:06:59.77,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,To make sure his automail's all tuned up and stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.06,0:07:02.23,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,You know, to prepare for the worst.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.23,0:07:03.81,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look at him later, Winry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.52,0:07:09.49,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,You made all his latest stuff, so I can't do the fine-tuning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.70,0:07:12.99,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.33,0:07:18.41,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.16,0:07:21.42,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So the people of Lior have gotten back up on their feet again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.08,0:07:23.58,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,That's a relief.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.58,0:07:25.04,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's been bugging me, to tell you the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.13,0:07:31.93,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So, why is Al with Major Miles?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.51,0:07:36.97,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I heard the people from Briggs are going to do something at the joint exercises in the east.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.47,0:07:41.18,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Al volunteered to join them, saying there might be something he could help out with.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.35,0:07:43.35,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.35,0:07:48.28,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Your dad went to Central ahead of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.65,0:07:53.91,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I heard he's in some slum called 'Kanama', so you should meet up with him to get the details.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.20,0:08:01.00,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,The Promised Day is coming up... right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.75,0:08:06.75,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I heard about that from Greed as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.34,0:08:13.80,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's a day when we may be able to get our bodies back,\N or a day when a great tragedy will strike this nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.30,0:08:18.14,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.68,0:08:20.31,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.77,0:08:24.69,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Take Granny and Den and escape to another country.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.98,0:08:28.65,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Are you telling me to run away?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.65,0:08:30.48,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Telling those close to you to escape makes it sound like you've already given up!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.03,0:08:33.95,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you stop the threat to this country?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.11,0:08:35.57,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I'll stop them!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.57,0:08:38.07,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,But there's a one in a million chance that it may not work!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.16,0:08:40.33,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Be 100% sure, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.45,0:08:44.62,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,They're planning to do something terrible, aren't they?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.62,0:08:47.33,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Beat them to a pulp and protect our country!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.79,0:08:52.30,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,And while you're at it, get your bodies back and return safe and sound!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.30,0:08:54.84,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I'll do {\i1}anything{\i0\fscx40} {\r} to make that happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.06,0:09:03.48,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Geez, you make it sound like a walk in the park.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.68,0:09:04.68,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.68,0:09:07.10,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,You're not acting like yourself-
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.81,0:09:08.86,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Ed!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.86,0:09:12.69,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Gosh, you're such an annoying woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.69,0:09:13.69,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Ed!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.87,0:09:24.25,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,Fine woman you have up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.62,0:09:27.50,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,She just sounds like she wants everything\Nin the world. Quite the greedy one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.50,0:09:31.29,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,When you get too greedy, it comes back to bite you in the behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.05,0:09:32.88,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,See this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.88,0:09:35.92,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to bring back the dead, and this was my reward.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.92,0:09:37.26,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,You really think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.63,0:09:43.72,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,"I long to see someone who died",\N"I want to be rich", "I want women"...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.72,0:09:45.93,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,"I want to protect the world"...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.93,0:09:48.02,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,They're all desires.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.65,0:09:50.27,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, wishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.44,0:09:55.11,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,If you ask me, there's neither 'right' nor 'wrong' when it comes to greed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.11,0:10:01.24,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx95}You humans go around ranking certain types of greed in order from good to bad, which makes you so hard to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.75,0:10:12.67,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,You're leaving {\i1}now{\i0\fscx40} {\r} of all times?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.67,0:10:16.80,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We were planning on leaving today anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.09,0:10:21.80,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for the tune-up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.93,0:10:28.77,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,If you ever happen to see Hohenheim, deliver Trisha's message for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.98,0:10:30.73,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.73,0:10:32.27,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Ed! I...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.27,0:10:34.73,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You stay hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.28,0:10:41.53,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I'll come home after putting an end to everything on the Promised Day, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.28,0:10:44.28,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,...wait for us with a freshly-baked apple pie. Deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.33,0:10:48.12,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Deal!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.21,0:11:00.01,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Work today took forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.18,0:11:03.47,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,But hey, is this really what we should be focusing on right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.10,0:11:05.64,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,The Promised Day is coming up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.81,0:11:07.35,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Not much else we can do!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.81,0:11:09.85,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor Marcoh and Scar haven't met up with us yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.56,0:11:13.19,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,Geez... where the hell are they?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.03,0:11:18.49,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.49,0:11:19.94,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, it's you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.20,0:11:22.45,Default,Jerso,0000,0000,0000,,"Hey, it's you guys"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.45,0:11:24.45,Default,Jerso,0000,0000,0000,,Where have you two been all this time?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.37,0:11:26.45,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.66,0:11:29.33,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Let's head over to Central.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.08,0:11:35.54,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,But something feels a little off.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.54,0:11:40.59,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,We used to be soldiers, but now we're working with an Ishbalan.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.59,0:11:41.88,Default,Jer,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.47,0:11:46.10,Default,Jer,0000,0000,0000,,For us, Amestris is our birthplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.10,0:11:47.56,Default,Jer,0000,0000,0000,,We've got family here as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.72,0:11:55.15,Default,Jer,0000,0000,0000,,But Scar, who used to rebel against the nation, is now working to protect it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.15,0:11:56.90,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get the wrong idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.90,0:11:59.11,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,My goal is not to protect this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.11,0:12:00.07,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,I'm working to change it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.45,0:12:05.95,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,I'm working in order for the people of this country to recognize the existence of the Ishbalans,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.95,0:12:09.99,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,a race that they denied.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.41,0:12:15.00,Default,Master,0000,0000,0000,,In order to change the world,\Nyou must start by changing yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.46,0:12:19.50,Default,Master,0000,0000,0000,,That's how it is, Amestrians.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.71,0:12:21.05,Default,Jer,0000,0000,0000,,Ishbalans?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.05,0:12:21.97,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.51,0:12:26.76,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,We weren't just dawdling about for months doing nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.01,0:12:30.77,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,They're comrades who share our goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.03,0:12:47.53,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,May this year's exercises be productive as always, Lieutenant General.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.16,0:12:53.16,Default,Grum,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad we're doing it in the east this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.71,0:12:56.62,Default,Grum,0000,0000,0000,,Joint exercises in the north are pretty tough for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.59,0:13:03.55,Default,Grum,0000,0000,0000,,Everything's ready on our end.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.34,0:13:05.97,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Ours, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.47,0:13:09.60,Default,Grum,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, a little problem has popped up...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.06,0:13:12.14,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,That being?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.44,0:13:19.73,Default,Grum,0000,0000,0000,,Little miss Bradley is here to observe as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.36,0:13:29.49,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I was expecting someone high up to watch over the practice, since it's right before the Promised Day...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.95,0:13:33.87,Default,Grum,0000,0000,0000,,We'll just have to figure something out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.97,0:13:54.22,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,There it is again...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.69,0:14:02.82,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,The delay between visions is gradually getting shorter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.98,0:14:05.24,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I have to hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.61,0:14:07.78,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I need to get my body back, or...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.63,0:14:23.46,Default,Glut,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I can smell him!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.46,0:14:27.01,Default,Glut,0000,0000,0000,,Smells like the Fullmetal Alchemist's little brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.88,0:14:30.01,Default,Glut,0000,0000,0000,,Running away?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.55,0:14:33.39,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't good!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.97,0:14:36.52,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I'm in no condition to fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.08,0:14:57.00,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,What's... this...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.00,0:15:04.92,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Talk about great timing...!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.89,0:15:22.90,Default,Selim,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to have you keep quiet until the Promised Day,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.52,0:15:25.48,Default,Selim,0000,0000,0000,,Alphonse Elric.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.54,0:15:46.63,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Good evening, Major General.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.38,0:15:51.59,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I've got no tea for the likes of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.85,0:15:59.47,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I may be able to take you out for dinner soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.47,0:16:02.27,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,So you finally plan to fulfill the promise from forever ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.27,0:16:11.28,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx95}'Large' doesn't even begin to describe this mansion.\NThe wealth of the Armstrong family never ceases to amaze me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.20,0:16:16.28,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,You could fit a company... no, even a full battalion in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.12,0:16:21.29,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,If something may happen to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.00,0:16:25.50,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,you can have the entire mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.50,0:16:27.75,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,It won't fit into my coffin, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.96,0:16:31.13,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,You're not going to give it to your brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.55,0:16:38.68,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I'd say you're the better choice... by a hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.06,0:16:41.56,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,That's quite an honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.27,0:16:46.60,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Belatedly...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.02,0:16:49.94,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,This is to congratulate you for becoming the head of the Armstrong family.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.24,0:16:55.61,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Hyacinths...?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.58,0:17:04.00,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,"Selim Bradley is a Homunculus."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.62,0:17:09.09,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Are you aware of what the Hyacinth represents?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.00,0:17:11.96,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.76,0:17:15.38,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Feminine beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.64,0:17:19.10,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need your flowers!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.14,0:17:24.18,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if you'll excuse me, Major General.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.90,0:17:29.15,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,You amateur.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.21,0:17:52.21,Default,Grum,0000,0000,0000,,This is annoying.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.21,0:17:57.34,Default,Grum,0000,0000,0000,,We should just aim a cannon at Bradley's tower and be done with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.34,0:17:58.59,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.97,0:17:59.93,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Major Miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.18,0:18:05.43,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,So we still don't have a clue as to where Alphonse Elric disappeared to...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.43,0:18:08.60,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. We're still searching, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.60,0:18:11.61,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be that he was captured?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.11,0:18:16.69,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,And the Promised Day is tomorrow...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.82,0:18:19.70,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Sire.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.37,0:18:22.74,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Major General Hakuro has arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.58,0:18:27.71,Default,Haku,0000,0000,0000,,Sire, there's something I need to inform you about Lieutenant General Grumman-
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.71,0:18:30.25,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,A coup d'etat using the Eastern army?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.75,0:18:33.25,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,We've already planned for such eventualities.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.67,0:18:37.76,Default,Haku,0000,0000,0000,,No, the joint practice is a bait.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.51,0:18:42.51,Default,Haku,0000,0000,0000,,The Ishbalan remnants will commit a terrorist act in Central,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.51,0:18:44.76,Default,Haku,0000,0000,0000,,now that defenses have weakened since Your Highness is here in the east.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.39,0:18:51.23,Default,Haku,0000,0000,0000,,Lieutenant General Grumman will use "terrorist suppression" as a pretense to invade Central.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.98,0:18:54.77,Default,Haku,0000,0000,0000,,He's planning on taking advantage of the confusion to take over Central Headquarters,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.40,0:18:57.40,Default,Haku,0000,0000,0000,,with the help of Colonel Mustang.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.50,0:19:09.96,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Just as Major General Hakuro stated,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.96,0:19:15.25,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,many Ishbalans have infiltrated Central vicinity over the past few days.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.55,0:19:26.72,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,I'm returning to Central.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.72,0:19:28.14,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,I'll leave matters here in your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.43,0:19:29.31,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.65,0:19:38.44,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,That damned Mustang... planning something outrageous.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.03,0:19:42.99,Default,Sol2,0000,0000,0000,,I thought we took care of him when we\Nseparated him from all of his useful men...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.75,0:19:55.75,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,The train stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.50,0:19:57.50,Default,Sol2,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.76,0:20:01.92,Default,Sol2,0000,0000,0000,,Sheep crossing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.92,0:20:03.84,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit, we're in a rush for time...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.39,0:20:14.40,Default,Sol2,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, they just left us!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.40,0:20:15.27,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.48,0:20:16.52,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.52,0:20:18.27,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Make him stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.79,0:20:39.13,Default,Char,0000,0000,0000,,The sheep on the tracks have been exterminated.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.13,0:20:41.71,Default,Char,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be heading to Central as planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.92,0:20:43.93,Default,Char,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.93,0:20:45.22,Default,Char,0000,0000,0000,,The Colonel is awaiting our arrival.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.22,0:20:46.39,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.72,0:20:47.76,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.77,0:20:54.23,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,You played right into their hands, Major General Hakuro.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.06,0:20:59.57,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,The train that was carrying the Führer President has been bombed!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.73,0:21:00.44,Default,Haku,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.50,0:21:17.12,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Everything begins tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.12,0:21:18.83,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Time to make our move,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.29,0:21:21.34,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Second Lieutenant Breda, Master Sergeant Fuery.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.84,0:21:23.76,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,No need for the "Second Lieutenant", ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.38,0:21:26.26,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,We're just plain old deserters now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.55,0:21:28.93,Default,Fuery,0000,0000,0000,,There goes my future...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.51,0:21:34.52,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have the Colonel take responsibility after everything's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.78,0:23:11.07,Default,Kle,0000,0000,0000,,The Führer President?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.32,0:23:13.53,Default,Fox,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way King Bradley could die...!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.91,0:23:16.20,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,We can't make assumptions just yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.20,0:23:17.79,Default,Fox,0000,0000,0000,,What has the investigation turned up?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.79,0:23:19.66,Default,Kle,0000,0000,0000,,The squadron has yet to reach the scene of the accident!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.66,0:23:22.12,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,As soon as their leader is gone, this happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.91,0:23:21.08,Default-alt,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Make them hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.08,0:23:22.12,Default-alt,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,Quit yelling!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.12,0:23:22.63,Default-alt,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,{\alpha&HFF&}PLACEHOLDER
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.12,0:23:23.75,Default-alt,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,This is not my job!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.04,0:23:24.79,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, they're nothing but an undisciplined mob.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.75,0:23:24.59,Default-alt,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,But...!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.59,0:23:26.96,Default-alt,Guy3,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't the time for this!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.96,0:23:30.30,Default-alt,Guy3,0000,0000,0000,,{\alpha&HFF&}PLACEHOLDER
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.96,0:23:29.26,Default-alt,Guy3,0000,0000,0000,,The supreme commander is missing!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.26,0:23:30.42,Default-alt,Harri,0000,0000,0000,,I know that!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.42,0:23:31.97,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,This may be my chance...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.22,0:23:41.02,Default,Frank,0000,0000,0000,,I never expected someone as important as you to visit this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.27,0:23:44.56,Default,Father,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.03,0:23:53.28,Default,Father,0000,0000,0000,,I'm still here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.62,0:24:00.25,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,What lurks in the shadows?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.58,0:24:03.96,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Demons? Beasts? Monsters?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.75,0:24:10.21,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,A black gust of wind saves our heroes who are faced with a crisis.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.42,0:24:15.72,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, Fullmetal Alchemist:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.72,0:24:19.35,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 47, Emissary of Darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.31,0:24:25.31,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Shed light on the heart of man. To an engulfing darkness.
